import pyspark

To create a DataFrame in PySpark, you can follow these steps:
1. Import the required PySpark modules
2. Create a SparkSession object
3. Define the schema for the DataFrame
4. Create a list of rows to populate the DataFrame
5. Create a DataFrame using the createDataFrame() method of the SparkSession object

from pyspark.sql.types import _parse_datatype_string

data=[(1,'Shiju'),(2,'Ryan')]
schema="id Integer ,Name String "
